PRETORIA - Even 24 years after democracy dawned in South Africa, place names and symbols honouring apartheid and colonial figures are still found in public spaces. Some say lessons can be drawn from the events that unfolded in Germany after the fall of Adolf Hitler at the end of World War II. READ: WC wants to change 'offensive' street names to honour Madiba Concerted efforts to reconstruct Germany kicked in, part of which was the removal of Nazi symbols across the country. As the country marks Freedom Day, eNCA's Lirandzu Themba takes a look at whether enough has been done to move South Africa beyond its dark past. Watch the full report above. eNCA